dc_title_s: Map of a portion of southeastern Wisconsin at the time of the formation of the first gravel terrace, showing the relations of the Lake Michigan Glacier, including the Delevan Lobe, to the Green Bay Glacier and of the moraines and attendant outwash deposits to the earlier drift deposits
dc_description_s: This digital map represents Plate X of William C. Alden's 1904 paper: 'The Delevan Lobe of the Lake Michigan Glacier of the Wisconsin stage of glaciation and associated phenomena'. Published by the United States Geological Survey as Professional Paper No. 34: https://doi.org/10.3133/pp34
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived map image held at the University of Wisconsin-Madison.
